{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContextProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"strictPosix","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, this mode is disabled."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict POSIX mode, the first non-argument parameter encountered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(eg: filename) terminates argument processing.  Remaining arguments"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are treated as non-options and are not attempted to be parsed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If strict POSIX mode is disabled then parsing is done in the GNU way"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"where option arguments can be freely mixed with non-options."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example, consider “ls foo -l”.  With GNU style parsing, this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will list “foo” in long mode.  In strict POSIX style, this will list","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the files named “foo” and “-l”.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It may be useful to force strict POSIX mode when creating “verb","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"style” command line tools.  For example, the “gsettings” command line","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tool supports the global option “–schemadir” as well as many"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subcommands (“get”, “set”, etc.) which each have their own set of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arguments.  Using strict POSIX mode will allow parsing the global","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"options up to the verb name while leaving the remaining options to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed by the relevant subcommand (which can be determined by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"examining the verb name, which should be present in argv[1] after"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontextprotocol\/set(strictposix:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Sets strict POSIX mode.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContextProtocol\/set(strictPosix:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"set(strictPosix:)","externalID":"s:4GLib21OptionContextProtocolPAAE3set11strictPosixySb_tF","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"strictPosix"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContextProtocol":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OptionContextProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontextprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContextProtocol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOptionContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct defines which options"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are accepted by the commandline option parser. The struct has only private"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fields and should not be directly accessed.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OptionContextProtocol"}],"title":"OptionContextProtocol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/OptionContextProtocol/set(strictPosix:)":{"type":"topic","title":"set(strictPosix:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/optioncontextprotocol\/set(strictposix:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"strictPosix","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets strict POSIX mode."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/OptionContextProtocol\/set(strictPosix:)","role":"symbol"}}}